as low as 10 miles an hour and as high as 35 miles an hour, which is definitely the

00:14:54.080 --> 00:14:58.840
traffic engineers have their work cut out for them, and you can use it for, like, evaluation

00:14:58.840 --> 00:15:02.599
of, like, okay, here's exactly where you need to drill down, and you can go from this

00:15:02.599 --> 00:15:10.599
big, big global Google Maps, Apple Maps view down to route 44 westbound in the afternoon

00:15:10.599 --> 00:15:17.320
peak is 5.5 miles an hour on this one thing, and we do it for every agency in the state.

00:15:17.320 --> 00:15:19.520
So all of this is public and online.

00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:24.200
I think I have the analysis site pulled up, so you can go browse these speed maps.

